                            "defaultConfiguration": {
                                "level": "warning"
                            },
                            "fullDescription": {
                                "text": "There's an HTTP request made with requests, but the raise_for_status() utility method isn't used. This can result in request errors going unnoticed and your code behaving in unexpected ways, such as if your authorization API returns a 500 error while you're only checking for a 401."
                            },
                            "help": {
                                "markdown": "There's an HTTP request made with requests, but the raise_for_status() utility method isn't used. This can result in request errors going unnoticed and your code behaving in unexpected ways, such as if your authorization API returns a 500 error while you're only checking for a 401.\n\n<b>References:</b>\n - [https://requests.readthedocs.io/en/master/api/#requests.Response.raise_for_status](https://requests.readthedocs.io/en/master/api/#requests.Response.raise_for_status)\n",
                                "text": "There's an HTTP request made with requests, but the raise_for_status() utility method isn't used. This can result in request errors going unnoticed and your code behaving in unexpected ways, such as if your authorization API returns a 500 error while you're only checking for a 401."
                            },
